tags.description:
[Webhooks](#tag/Webhooks) are used in the system to allow developers and integration platforms (such as [Zapier](https://zapier.com/)) to subscribe to a [Webhook Event](#tag/Webhook-Events), such as a person.updated or person.created event.

  When the [Webhook Event](#tag/Webhook-Events) is triggered, the system will send a payload to the endpoint specified when creating the [Webhook](#tag/Webhooks).

  These [Webhooks](#tag/Webhooks) follow the [Rest Hook](https://resthooks.org/) pattern.

  The payload of these [Webhooks](#tag/Webhooks) are in the following example structure:

    {

      "id": "{webhookId}",

      "event": "training.created",

      "links": {

        "self": "https://api.intellihr.io/trainings/{trainingId}"

      },

      "timestamp": "2019-09-25T05:51:35Z"

    }
